<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>DogPals - About</title>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
  <%= csp_meta_tag %>

  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbo-track': 'reload' %>
  <%= javascript_importmap_tags %>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>The vision for DogPals is to create a welcoming, efficient, and impactful platform that connects dogs with potential adopters. The website aims to be a trusted resource for dog adoption, providing detailed information, easy navigation, and a supportive community for both adopters and shelters.</p>

  <section>
    <h2>1.1 - Describe Datasets</h2>
    <h3>Selected Data Sources:</h3>
    
    <h4>Dog Listings Database:</h4>
    <p>
      <strong>Description:</strong> This dataset contains information about dogs available for adoption, including their names, breeds, ages, descriptions, and photos.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Structure:</strong> Each dog has attributes such as id, name, breed, age, description, photo_url, shelter_id.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Tables and Columns:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>dogs: id, name, breed, age, description, photo_url, shelter_id</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p><strong>Data Source:</strong> The dog data was sourced using the DogAPI and generated using the Faker gem.</p>


    <h4>User Profiles Database:</h4>
    <p>
      <strong>Description:</strong> This dataset includes user information, profiles, and saved favorite dogs.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Structure:</strong> Each user has attributes such as id, username, email, password_digest, profile_photo, favorite_dog_ids.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Tables and Columns:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>users: id, username, email, password_digest, profile_photo</li>
        <li>favorites: user_id, dog_id</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p><strong>Data Source:</strong> Custom made faker gem data for user profiles.</p>

    <h4>Shelter/Rescue Database:</h4>
    <p>
      <strong>Description:</strong> This dataset contains information about animal shelters and rescues, including their profiles and listed dogs.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Structure:</strong> Each shelter has attributes such as id, name, location, contact_info, website_url.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Tables and Columns:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>shelters: id, name, location, contact_info, website_url</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p><strong>Data Source:</strong> Custom made faker gem data for shelters.</p>

    <h4>Adoption Application Database:</h4>
    <p>
      <strong>Description:</strong> This dataset includes adoption applications submitted by users for specific dogs.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Structure:</strong> Each application has attributes such as id, user_id, dog_id, status, submitted_at.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Tables and Columns:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>applications: id, user_id, dog_id, status, submitted_at</li>
      </ul>
    </p>

    <h3>Integration:</h3>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>The <strong>shelter_id</strong> in the dogs table links each dog to a shelter.</li>
        <li>The <strong>user_id</strong> in the applications table links each application to a user.</li>
        <li>The <strong>dog_id</strong> in the applications table links each application to a specific dog.</li>
        <li>The <strong>favorite_dog_ids</strong> in the users table links users to their favorite dogs through the favorites table.</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Entity-Relationship Diagram (ERD)</h2>
    <%= image_tag 'erd_image.png', alt: 'ERD' %>
  </section>
</body>
</html>

